         <abstract id="aspace_5a571492313fd667da75a85936c2417f">Fifteen manuscript ships' logs, letter books, and other notes kept by William Whittemore Low while serving various assignments aboard United States Navy vessels, 1822-1876 (bulk 1841-1876).

Ships represented include the <title>
               <part>USS Franklin, USS Missouri, USS Decatur, USS Columbus, USS Portsmouth, USS Octorara, USS Oneida, USS Mohican,</part>
            </title> and <title>
               <part>USS Tennessee</part>
            </title>.

Logs for the <title>
               <part>USS Decatur</part>
            </title> and <title>
               <part>USS Portsmouth</part>
            </title> were created during the ships' patrol of the African coast to suppress the slave trade. Logs for the <title>
               <part>USS Octorara</part>
            </title> and <title>
               <part>USS Oneida</part>
            </title> were created during the ships' use in the American Civil War.</abstract>
